description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity to join and to lead a team of multi-disciplinary professionals working with patients who are under the care of the Acute Psychiatric Liaison team and the Persistent Physical Symptoms Service. You will be required to be an innovative, flexible and enthusiastic team leader ensuring the effective delivery of evidence based and person-centered care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The suitable candidate’s will be experienced to provide both clinical leadership as well as operational management of a service and will have experience in service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong team working principles are essential and you will work in partnership with local and regional agencies, including acute hospital services , Social services, community services, volunteers, Service Users, Families, and other supporting agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must ensure that prior to applying they have agreement from their current line manager that they can be released on a secondment basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In the event that permanent funding is secured for this post the successful applicant will be confirmed in post on a permanent basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Bell, Service Manager at joannebell@nhs.net 01913333550&lt;/p&gt;
